{
    "attributes": {
        "action": "Review legislation to improve regulation for online betting tipsters",
        "additional_details": "We believe betting tipster services should be regulated for several reasons, primarily to protect consumers and ensure fair practices in an industry prone to exploitation. We also support better regulation to prevent fraud and misrepresentation: there are concerns that tipsters may exaggerate or falsify their success rates to attract clients, misleading bettors about potential profits. We believe stronger regulation can enforce transparency, requiring tipsters to provide verified records of their performance.",
        "background": "We urge the Government to review current legislation to improve regulation for online betting tipsters, including looking into heavily fining or shutting down tipsters that do not follow strict regulation guidelines.",
